name: Coordinates.altitudeAccuracy
description: The GeolocationCoordinates.altitudeAccuracy read-only property is a strictly positive double representing the accuracy, with a 95% confidence level, of the altitude expressed in meters. This value is null if the implementation doesn't support measuring altitude.
